Organization = {ACM Special Interest Grp Design Automat; IEEE Circuits \& Syst Soc; IEEE
   Council Elect Design Automat; EIC; Incheon Tourism Org; Korea Tourism
   Org; Cadence Design Syst Inc},
Abstract = {Neural Architecture Search (NAS) has become the de fecto tools in the
   industry in automating the design of deep neural networks for various
   applications, especially those driven by mobile and edge devices with
   limited computing resources. The emerging large language models (LLMs),
   due to their prowess, have also been incorporated into NAS recently and
   show some promising results. This paper conducts further exploration in
   this direction by considering three important design metrics
   simultaneously, i.e., model accuracy, fairness, and hardware deployment
   efficiency. We propose a novel LLM-based NAS framework, FL-NAS, in this
   paper, and show experimentally that FL-NAS can indeed find
   high-performing DNNs, beating state-of-the-art DNN models by
   orders-of-magnitude across almost all design considerations.},
